where our tools for understanding reality

28
00:01:13,620 --> 00:01:17,400
subtly replace reality itself.

29
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:18,400
It's a huge problem.

30
00:01:18,540 --> 00:01:19,100
It really is.

31
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:21,800
It's a journey into how we build our mental models,

32
00:01:22,180 --> 00:01:25,140
the precise mechanisms of how they inevitably break down,

33
00:01:25,140 --> 00:01:28,220
and crucially, how we can perform maintenance on them

34
00:01:28,220 --> 00:01:32,040
so we don't end up living inside, you know, a beautiful delusion.

35
00:01:32,460 --> 00:01:37,080
To guide us through this, we're examining a deeply fascinating single source today.

