Oh, incredibly dense.

38
00:01:39,260 --> 00:01:43,260
It's a paper from May 2026 by an independent researcher named Flyxion.

39
00:01:43,620 --> 00:01:46,280
And the title itself really gives you a sense of the stakes.

40
00:01:46,420 --> 00:01:46,820
It's called,

41
00:01:46,820 --> 00:01:56,640
What makes this text so gripping isn't just the density of the subject matter, though.

